  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a large pan, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add the minced pork and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chopped onion and minced garlic to the pan and cook until the onion is translucent, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the rest-meat, soy sauce, sugar, salt, and black pepper to the pan and stir to combine.",
    "Transfer the pan to the preheated oven and roast for 20-25 minutes, or until the meat is cooked through and lightly browned on top.",
    "Remove the pan from the oven and sprinkle with chopped scallions.",
    "Serve the Light Filipino Pork Pan-Canton hot, garnished with additional scallions if desired."
